==Introduction==
The '''Related Data''' widgets '''displays a list of all pages which refer (link) to the currently displayed data entity'''.


The widget is displayed only on the View Page:
* creates a new section called '''"Related Information"''' containing a bar with variable number of Tabs
* for each '''Source Concept''' which refers to the current '''Target Concept''' page (see [[Help:Page Property|Page Property]] for more details):
** creates a new Tab if there are any Source Concept pages pointing to the current Target Concept page
** uses the Source Concept name as a Tab Label
** allows to apply different styles to rendered list


Note that the [[Help:Reference|Reference]] widget supports similar functionality.
Both of them display the list(s) of pages referring to the current page.
The [[Help:Reference|Reference]] widget however '''displays only ONE list of pages''' from a specific Source Concept with specific Property referring to the current page.
The "Reference" widget might be placed along other Concept properties and widgets, thus allowing to display the list in any place on the page.
The list displayed using "Reference" widget is removed from the "Related Data" tabs.



==Definition==
There are two configuration options:
* hide/show the entire widget
* hide/show the selected associations


<pre>
<concept name="{CONCEPT}">
  <structure>
  </structure>

  <relatedData hide="{HIDE}">
    <hide concept="{ASSOCIATION CONCEPT NAME}" property="{ASSOCIATION PROPERTY NAME}"/>
    ...
  </relatedData>

</concept>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {HIDE}
| A Booelan flag indicating if RelatedData widget should be displayed. Default: true.
|-
! {ASSOCIATION CONCEPT NAME}
| An association to be removed from the RelatedData widget: a name of related concept.
|-
! {ASSOCIATION PROPERTY NAME}
| An association to be removed from the RelatedData widget: a name of related property.
|}


To customize the rendering of the list of pages referring to the current page add the "style" element to the referring Page Property of the Source Concept:

<pre>
<concept name="{SOURCE}">
  <structure>
    <property name="Property 1"/>
    <property name="Property 2"/>
    <property name="Property 3"/>
    <property name="{REFERRING PROPERTY NAME}" refersTo="{TARGET}">
      <relatedData format="{FORMAT}">
        <columns>
          <column name="{COLUMN NAME}"/>
          <column name="{COLUMN NAME}"/>
          <column name="{COLUMN NAME}"/>
        </columns>
      </relatedData>
    </property>
  </structure>
</concept>

<concept name="{TARGET}">
  <structure>
    <property name="Property A"/>
    <property name="Property B"/>
    <property name="Property C"/>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {SOURCE}
| A name of the Source Concept.
|-
! {TARGET}
| A name of the Target Concept.
|-
! {REFERRING PROPERTY NAME}
| A name of the Property of 'Page' type in the Source Concept which refers to the Target Concept.
|-
! {FORMAT}
| A format type used to render referring Source Concept pages. The following options are allowed:
* table. The "table" layout displays a table with referring pages. The first column displays a Source page name, and the following columns display the values of the properties defined in the {COLUMNS} attribute.
* list. The "link" layout displays a list of referring pages. The main list heading displays a Source page name, and under it the values of the properties defined in the {COLUMNS} attribute.
* link. The "link" layout displays simple list of links to the referring Source pages.
|-
! {COLUMN NAME}
| A name of the column to be displayed next to the page name.
|}



==Example==
Customize the list of associations to be displayed on the page:
<pre>
<concept name="Exercise">
  ....
  <relatedData hide="true"/>
</concept>

or

<concept name="Exercise">
  ....
  <relatedData>
    <hide concept="Test Case" property="Is tested during"/>
  </relatedData>
</concept>


</pre>

Customize the lists displayed in the tabs.
<pre>
<concept name="Capability Configuration" ...>          <!-- Source Concept -->
  <structure>
    <property name="Title"/>
    <property name="Description"/>
    <property name="Is hosted on"/>
    <property name="Is lead by" refersTo="User">       <!-- Referring Page Property -->
      <relatedData>                                    <!-- style for Related Data -->
        <columns>
          <column name="Title"/>
          <column name="Description"/>
          <column name="Is hosted on"/>
        </columns>
      </relatedData>
    </property>
  </structure>
</concept>

<concept name="User" ...>                              <!-- Target Concept -->
  <structure>
    <property name="First name"/>
    <property name="Last name"/>
    <property name="Organization"/>
    <property name="Function"/>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>


==User Interface==
The "Related Data" widget is displayed only on the View Page of the Target Concept ("User" in the example above).

